\begin_layout Standard
The brick implementation of the Kalman filter can be improved by switching
 to a faster matrix class library to reduce the iteration runtime.
 One could switch to using single point arithmetic instead of double, as
 it has more than enough of accuracy for our application anyway.
 Even a integer point solution could be adopted, as was done with the particle
 filter.
 That could probably have made the iteration runtime a lot shorter.
\end_layout

